snippet.textDisplay: Great job! I've played with those cheap kits before, we got 240whp out of a stock Mini Cooper with the same snail you're using, and all we did was change the fuel pump, strap a small intercooler on the rad, and run some hoses (basically everything you guys did). I think it actually took longer to tune than it did to install, because I had access to a proper lift. The only downside, apart from worse fuel economy and needing premium gas, is that it does have some lag, but that's what downshifting is for. 😆 Still, it's a really fun little car that only cost $2500 all in, and that includes a used Sparco racing seat, a coat of neon blue plasti-dip, and fresh tires.
